    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-06T21:17:56+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-06T21:17:56+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-06T11:47:56Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-06T11:47:56Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A cold front will pass over the southeast overnight followed by a high-pressure system building south of the state on Tuesday. The high will then move east on Wednesday allowing an upper trough to bring instability to southern parts of the state during the day, persisting into Thursday. The upper trough will precede a vigorous cold front that is forecast to move over South Australia Thursday afternoon. A cooler southwest to southerly flow will gradually moderate as a stronger high-pressure system moves in from the west from Friday to be south of the state on Sunday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW014" description="North East Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-06T21:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-07T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-06T11:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-06T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Clear. Winds southeast to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-07T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-06T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Slight chance of a shower south of Yunta, most likely in the late afternoon and evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds southeast to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h becoming light in the middle of the day then becoming southeast to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the early afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 17 and 21 with daytime temperatures reaching 28 to 36.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:10am to 3:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 8 [Very High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Medium chance of showers south of Yunta, most likely in the morning and afternoon. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending east to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h in the early morning then tending northwest to northeasterly 20 to 30 km/h in the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 15 and 21 with daytime temperatures reaching 28 to 37.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Medium chance of showers south of Yunta, most likely in the afternoon and evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds northwest to northeasterly 25 to 40 km/h tending northwesterly during the day then tending northwest to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 19 and 23 with daytime temperatures reaching the mid to high 30s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-10T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Slight chance of a shower south of Yunta in the morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds south to southwesterly 25 to 40 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 17 and 22 with daytime temperatures reaching 24 to 36.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
